text: Minnesota's 1st congressional district is located in southern Minnesota from the border with South Dakota to the border with Wisconsin. It is a rural district with a history of agriculture, however it is located near the Rochester area. The district is also home to several of Minnesota's major mid- sized cities, including Rochester, Mankato, Winona, Austin, Owatonna, Albert Lea, Red Wing, New Ulm, Worthington, and Lake City. It is represented by Republican Brad Finstad. ==References== Category:Minnesota
